    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "aa7d7da5_b7002c0a",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/generators.star",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 380,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-10T01:11:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I realized we have fields in the scheduler that specify \u0027properties\u0027 and \u0027tags\u0027 to pass to buildbucket when scheduler triggers a build.\n\nSince we decided to hardcode relations between buildbucket.Builder and scheduler.Job to be 1-to-1, it means we can define all properties directly in the buildbucket config, EXCEPT the following situation will no longer be possible:\n\n1. There\u0027s a builder B.\n2. When it is triggered through Buildbucket it by default gets properties {\u0027k\u0027: \u0027v\u0027}, since this is what in cr-buildbucket.cfg.\n3. When it is triggered through Scheduler it by default gets properties {\u0027k\u0027: \u0027overridden\u0027}, since this is what in luci-scheduler.cfg.\n\nShould we care?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 380,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 380,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "441646694b112ddd636112dbe1a36a577d0ad2f0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "55111a03_05d286e3",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/generators.star",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 380,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-10T02:14:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think that\u0027s rare enough to not care; if really really necessary, clients can still override this using lucicfg guts, right?",
      "parentUuid": "aa7d7da5_b7002c0a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 380,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 380,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "441646694b112ddd636112dbe1a36a577d0ad2f0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "26ec6894_6dad4d2b",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/generators.star",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 380,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-10T05:03:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, but this is the very last, ugliest option.\n\nI forced to, we can potentially do some crap like: \n\ncore.builder(\n   properties \u003d {\n     \u0027k1\u0027: core.property(\u0027val\u0027, only_when_triggered\u003dTrue),\n     \u0027k2\u0027: \u0027v\u0027,  # gets wrapped in core.property automatically\n   },\n)\n\nOr introduce new \u0027triggered_properties\u0027 field. Or something other equivalent to it.\n\nI\u0027ll look through existing luci-scheduler.cfg configs tomorrow to see whether there\u0027ll be any problems. If no, I think we can ignore this regression for now and deal with it only when asked.",
      "parentUuid": "55111a03_05d286e3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 380,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 380,
        "endChar": 48
      },
